description: This raster layer depicts low lying areas at risk of sea-level rise and coastal flooding. Intertidal and maximum spring high tide extents are shown in dark to cyan, to 4 m above Mean Low Water. Above this, high (4-6 m above MLW in red), moderate (6-7 m above MLW in yellow), and low (8-9 m above MLW in green).
name: Sea Level Rise vulnearbility
